Name:
loudness set -- set the loudness from the system

Synopsis:
LOUDNESS SET number

Description:
Set the loudness from the system to the given number.  

Example:
ss=-70
sz=20
for i = 1 to 5 
	LOUDNESS SET ss
	x=peek("loudness")
	print x
	wait 2
	LOUDNESS SET sz
	x=peek("loudness")
	print x
	wait 2
next i

Explanation:

In the example above, the volume was turned up and down every 2 seconds

Related: sound play, sound stop, peek("loudness")